# Keep PHI and secrets OUT of the build context / image.
#   *.db  -> SQLite databases contain PHI (patient PII + eligibility answers)
#   .env  -> runtime secrets (SECRET_KEY, DATABASE_URL); injected at runtime, never baked
# Everything below is excluded from `docker build` so it can never enter a layer.

# Local virtualenv — rebuilt inside the image from requirements.txt
.venv

# Python bytecode caches (recursive: also nested ones like routers/__pycache__)
**/__pycache__

# PHI: SQLite databases (app.db, test_*.db) must never be copied into the image
*.db

# Secret: real environment file. .env.example is kept on purpose as a template.
.env

# Dev-only seeder: ships hardcoded credentials (admin123/coord123/nurse123).
# Must never be present in the image — it would bake known logins into prod.
seed_users.py

# Test artifacts and suite — not needed in the runtime image
.pytest_cache
tests
conftest.py
